UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1440
1 AN ACT relating to malicious distribution of images without consent.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 531 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) A person is guilty of malicious distribution of images without consent when:
6 (a) He or she uses a computer to intentionally distribute to any website or
7 application, an image, including a publicly available image, without the
8 consent of the person depicted, and does so with the intent to:
9 1. Sexually arouse or sexually gratify another person;
10 2. Degrade, exploit, or abuse the person depicted; or
11 3. Invite or encourage comments from another person that would
12 express intent or fantasies that are sexual, abusive, physically
13 punishing, or otherwise illegal toward or involving the person
14 depicted; and
15 (b) The disclosure would cause a reasonable person to suffer harm.
16 (2) This section shall not apply to internet service providers or telecommunications
17 services, or interactive computer services as defined in 47 U.S.C. sec. 230(f)(2),
18 for content solely provided by another person.
19 (3) Malicious distribution of images without consent is a Class B misdemeanor.
20 (4) Notwithstanding KRS 17.500 to 17.580, a conviction under this section shall not
21 result in the offender being deemed a registrant or being required to register as a
22 sex offender.
23 (5) For purposes of this section, "consent" means the consent to transmission of
24 images to a specific recipient or any website or application. Consent to the
25 creation of the image does not, by itself, constitute consent to the distribution of
26 the image.
